        <Document ID="2C895337-6E1C-412D-8A18-51DE64405412">
            <Title>弹性Elasticity</Title>
            <Text>Elasticity is a measure of how sensitive one variable is in relation to another. It is used to test the effect that changes in price and income have on supply and demand.
The concept of price elasticity of demand measures the responsiveness of changes in quantity demanded to price changes of a given product. Goods that have a price elasticity of less than 1 are said to be inelastic, while those with price elasticity greater than 1 are said to be elastic. Necessities like water are considered inelastic since demand for them remains largely the same, even when their price increases dramatically. Similarly, income elasticity of demand relates changes in demand to changes in income.
弹性是一个变量对另一个变量敏感程度的度量。 它用来测试价格和收入变化对供求的影响。
需求价格弹性的概念衡量了对一个给定产品的价格变化所要求的数量变化的反应。 价格弹性小于1的商品被认为是非弹性的，而价格弹性大于1的商品被认为是弹性的。 像水这样的需求被认为是无弹性的，因为即使价格急剧上涨，对它们的需求也大体上保持不变。 同样，需求的收入弹性也将需求的变化与收入的变化联系起来。</Text>
