            <Title>供需定律Laws of supply and demand</Title>
            <Text>The law of demand states that there’s an inverse relationship between the price of a good and the quantity of the good demanded. Specifically, as the price of a good increases, the demand for it decreases. The income level of the buyer, the price of the good and the availability of substitutes are all factors that influence the level of demand.
The law of supply, on the other hand, reveals a positive relationship between the price of a good and the quantity supplied. In other words, an increase in the price of an item results in a corresponding increase in the quantity of that item. Price levels, input expenses and technological costs to produce a good are all factors that influence supply.
Supply and demand can behave quite differently in the stock market, however. For example, using the law of demand, if a company’s stock price were to drop well below a rational determination of its intrinsic value, investors should be eager to purchase more shares in that company, right? Not always! Companies can be grossly mispriced in the markets for long periods of time with little or no attention from investors. Remember our discussion about investment psychology earlier in the book?
Not surprisingly, the opposite reaction frequently occurs when stock prices increase. Common sense would lead you to expect a fall in demand. Wrong again! It seems that investors can’t shake their infinite optimism when a stock is racing ahead of itself; they can’t stop themselves from wanting to participate. Irrational behavior to be sure, but it’s observed frequently in the markets.
需求定律指出，商品的价格与所要求的商品的数量之间存在反比关系。具体而言，随着商品价格的上涨，对商品的需求也随之下降。买方的收入水平，商品的价格以及代用品的可用性都是影响需求水平的因素。
另一方面，供给规律揭示了货物价格与供应量之间的正相关关系。换句话说，物品价格的增加导致物品数量的相应增加。价格水平，投入费用和生产商品的技术成本都是影响供应的因素。
然而，供求关系在股票市场上的表现可能会有所不同。例如，根据需求定律，如果公司的股票价格远低于其内在价值的合理确定，投资者就应该急于购买该公司的股票，对吗？不总是！投资者很少或根本没有注意到公司可能在很长一段时间内严重错位市场。还记得我们之前关于投资心理学的讨论吗？
毫不奇怪，当股价上涨时，经常出现相反的情况。常识会导致你期望需求下降。又错了！当股票超前时，投资者似乎不能动摇他们的无限乐观;他们不能阻止自己想参与。非理性的行为是肯定的，但在市场上经常出现。</Text>
