            <Title>机会成本Opportunity costs</Title>
            <Text>The true cost of an item being purchased, or time spent on a particular activity, is what you give up to get that item or do that activity. This cost includes not only money spent, but also the economic benefits you chose to forgo because you bought that particular item and can no longer buy another one instead.
When you purchase an investment, you commit yourself to a certain course, even though other possible investments in the market might have earned you more money in the long run. These lost investment opportunities can result in a significant loss of utility. Economics teaches us the importance of managing our finite resources well—and that includes carefully considering the true cost of the opportunities that come our way.
购买物品的真实成本，或花费在特定活动上的时间，是你放弃获取该物品或进行该活动的原因。 这笔费用不仅包括花费，还包括您选择放弃的经济利益，因为您购买了特定物品，而不能再购买另一个物品。
当你购买一项投资时，即使在市场上其他可能的投资可能会为你赢得更多的钱， 这些失去的投资机会可能导致效用的显着损失。 经济学教会我们管理我们有限的资源的重要性，包括仔细考虑来自我们的方式的机会的真实成本。</Text>
